website:https://happyspaces.com.au meta title:Happy Spaces - Close To Home Coworking Spaces meta description:Close to home coworking space and business community in Torquay. Meeting, workshop and event spaces. Happy Spaces - Close To Home Coworking Spaces Work close to home, in your community, near the people you love. Happy Spaces coworking spaces are where genuine connection and wellbeing meets your local work space. Join an inspiring and collaborative group of locally and globally experienced professionals. Close to home coworking space and business community Level 1, 4 – 6 Gilbert Street, Our Torquay coworking space is in the hub of the village, overlooking main beach. At its heart, the space is for local professionals, entrepreneurs and small businesses who want to work close to home and experience deeper community connection, collaboration and belonging. The space features a homely, locally inspired and sourced design with mostly recycled and repurposed materials.   /  Founder - Future Giving & Fuck Giving I have somehow acquired a few cheeky nicknames which include The Sustainability Ninja, Fuckgiver, and The Purpose Hacker.   /  Founder & Director - Happy Spaces In May 2016, I was sitting by myself in our first empty space in Hampton... thinking...well... Happy Spaces and Happy Brands are registered trademarks of the Happy Spaces Group Pty Ltd. 2023 © All rights reserved. website:https://happyspaces.com.au/vision/ meta title:Our Vision - Happy Spaces meta description:N/A At Happy, we believe that life thrives locally and holistic wellbeing is success. Our core purpose of creating community connection, belonging and wellbeing is our ongoing motivation. Making space for connected local communities We create spaces that bring together local people and businesses with connection, collaboration and belonging. Our spaces are based on proven community sizes and optimal conditions for organic connection. We believe that living matters and strive to invest in our purpose and values in the every day moments and as we look forward. The Happy values inspire everything we do and guide our path, decisions and partnerships. Authentic relationships of depth, diversity and integrity Open minds and hearts to experiences that inspire positive change and development Committed to the healthy existence of the individual, the community and the environment Holistic balance in all areas of life Our passion for discovery and sense of adventure help us better understand and impact the communities we live in and inform our decisions. We launched our spaces in local places so you can work close to home, gain back valuable hours of your life everyday, connect to your community and collaborate with other professionals. There’s plenty happening out there in our local communities; great people, activities, event and exciting businesses. Close To Home Coworking - Happy Spaces We launched our spaces in local places so you can work close to home, gain back valuable hours of your life everyday, connect to your community and collaborate with other professionals. There’s plenty happening out there in our local communities; great people, activities, event and exciting businesses. Anything can happen, we’ve seen it. At Happy, we're dedicated to community connection, here's a few reasons why we do what we do; * Working close to home is proven to make you happier * Community connection and belonging is key to your wellbeing * Big things happen in small spaces. We base our spaces on optimal community sizes, because it's proven to create quality relationships, collaboration, creativity and new opportunities Also, here's some fun facts about our members; 94% have seen increased happiness working close to home 40% have generated new business (that we can measure directly) 75% enjoy a commute time less than 15 minutes Join a connected, inspiring and collaborative group of locally and globally experienced professionals. You’ll be amazed at the individuals, organisations, community and opportunities that come from working at Happy Spaces. Oh, and another thing, our community really know how to balance work and play. Scotty has lived a remarkably unique life. During his youth, he was fortunate to travel extensively with his parents from different hemispheres who founded an international textile company. Their family business Linen House has been at the core of his professional career. Sue has over 15 years in industry, with experience across various therapeutic areas, including cardiovascular, oncology, haematology, immunology and infectious diseases. In 2019 I landed my dream role, CEO of KidNest, a clever and simple concept, now a business, with “the potential to shift the Australian economy”. In this role I am learning as fast as a newborn as I flex my diverse skills - leadership, strategic and creative direction, experiential marketing, producing and quality management, and combine them with my passion, energy, network and ability to influence, to land our Pilot Program in City of Port Phillip in August 2020.   /  Director - Straight Out Digital I get digital and I'm not afraid to brag about it. Gilbert Street overlooking the beach. Meeting, workshop and event spaces. Coworking Space Torquay - Work Close To Home At Happy Spaces Our Torquay coworking space is in the hub of the village, overlooking main beach. At its heart, the space is for local professionals, entrepreneurs and small businesses who want to work close to home and experience deeper community connection, collaboration and belonging. The space features a homely, locally inspired and sourced design with mostly recycled and repurposed materials. OUR COWORKING SPACE IN TORQUAY IS ALL ABOUT CONNECTION, COLLABORATION AND BELONGING. There’s plenty happening out there locally. Our great community shares some of their stories of connection and collaboration. Anything can happen. We’ve seen it. Big things happen in small spaces. We base our spaces on optimal community sizes, because it’s proven to create quality connection, friendships and collaboration. Not only that, working close to home is proven to make you happier, so we’re right in the main village, close to everything you need. Big things happen in small spaces. We base our spaces on optimal community sizes, because it’s proven to create quality connection, friendships and collaboration. Not only that, working close to home is proven to make you happier, so we’re right in the main village, close to everything you need. We also have our 12 meter balcony overlooking the beach which is a great place to break out to for chats, food and drinks. Ripple Surf Coast is bringing together local impact organisations, businesses and investors in Torquay to discover and celebrate organisations using their venture as a force for good and creating positive impact in the Surf Coast, Geelong and Bellarine regions with our Surf Coast Impact Pitch Party. FLIRTING WITH PURPOSE – BUSINESS AS A FORCE FOR GOOD Our Flirting with Purpose connection events are full of connection and networking activities and feature the global B Corporation movement and local businesses at the different stages of their journeys.  Come, meet and mingle with businesses who are doing it already, those who want to step it up and those who are new to it all. FLIRTING WITH PURPOSE – BUSINESS AS A FORCE FOR GOOD Our Flirting with Purpose connection events are full of connection and networking activities and feature the global B Corporation movement and local businesses at the different stages of their journeys.  Come, meet and mingle with businesses who are doing it already, those who want to step it up and those who are new to it all. In The Flow Photography is a creative & professional photography business specialising in authentic & compelling imagery for people and brands across Melbourne & the Surf Coast, Victoria.   /  Rachael Byrne / Happy Spaces Rachael is our Torquay Community Manager, all the way from Scotland and now calling Torquay home. In 2019 I landed my dream role, CEO of KidNest, a clever and simple concept, now a business, with “the potential to shift the Australian economy”. In this role I am learning as fast as a newborn as I flex my diverse skills - leadership, strategic and creative direction, experiential marketing, producing and quality management, and combine them with my passion, energy, network and ability to influence, to land our Pilot Program in City of Port Phillip in August 2020. Mum of 2 and wife of 1, enthusiastic life doer, love a laugh and a cheeky glass of wine, will try anything once, optimistic big picture person, often time poor! I really hope people want to work close to home. I'm the founder of Happy Spaces, thanks to you all for joining us and making it the community it is.
